Mwana thought he had given the Dockers the lead in the 52nd minute but his header hit the goalpost, before goalkeeper Njung'e saved his other attempt moments laterBageya's impact in the match was felt immediately, as he picked Kimani upfront with a cross-field pass, and the skipper made no mistake in giving his side the lead in the 59th minuteAs the visitors were protesting the call by the centre referee, City Stars launched a counter attack, which saw captain Odhiambo score in his own net while attempting to clear Davis Agesa's dangerous cross Nairobi City Stars Friday bounced back to winning ways with a 2-0 win over Bandari in a BetKing Premier League (BPL) match at Moi International Sports Centre, Kasarani in Nairobi.
Anthony Kimani handed City Stars the lead in the 59th minute before Bandari's captain Bernard Odhiambo scored into his own net ten minutes later to sealed the hosts second win of the season.



