In their opening match of the season, City Stars beat Nzoia Sugar 2-0 at Narok Stadium. City Stars coach Sanjin Alagic was elated by the win against a tough Bandari side. 
"In their first match they (Bandari) won against Sofapaka and then drew against Tusker. They are a very good club in the Kenya Premier League and so it is a joy to beat them. Next match we will even play better," said the Bosnian.
Bandari coach Ken Odhiambo, who failed to beat his former employers, lamed poor officiating for the loss.



