"Some of the calls that were made in the match are exactly opposite of what I know. We lost our chances, they used theirs well though I do not recognise the second goal because it was scored when my players were complaining about the call by the referee to cancel our goal," said Odhiambo. 
After a strong start from both sides, City Stars came close to taking the lead in the in the 19th minute, when unmarked Herit Mungai attempted to beat Bandari goalkeeper Justin Ndikumana with a shot at his far right before Yema Mwana forced the host's goalkeeper Steven Njung'e to a save moments later.
Bandari looked to have taken control of the match and in the 35th minute, William Wadri - who started after coming in as a substitute in their barren draw against Tusker last weekend - was unlucky after his header from Abdallah Hassan's corner went wide.



