Bageya impact
Hassan exposed City Stars' defence with another corner in the 42nd minute, but no red shirt connected to his delivery inside the box.
Mwana thought he had given the Dockers the lead in the 52nd minute but his header hit the goalpost, before goalkeeper Njung'e saved his other attempt moments later.
City Stars coach Alagic sought to improve the momentum of his side by bringing in Ezekiel Odera and Jimmy Bageya for Oliver Maloba and Timothy Ouma respectively.
Bageya's impact in the match was felt immediately, as he picked Kimani upfront with a cross-field pass, and the skipper made no mistake in giving his side the lead in the 59th minute. 
Danson Namasaka thought he had levelled the score for Bandari in the 68th minute after he turned well to beat goalkeeper Njuguna with a low shot, but the goal was cancelled for offside.
As the visitors were protesting the call by the centre referee, City Stars launched a counter attack, which saw captain Odhiambo score in his own net while attempting to clear Davis Agesa's dangerous cross.
The win took City Stars tally to six points while Bandari remain on four points. A win for Bandari will send them top of the table with seven points. Gor Mahia chairman pours cold water on Sh800m deal that will tie down clubs for at least seven years. He served in former president Daniel Moi's cabinet. BBI secretariat cleaned up the 5.2 million signatures that endorsed the Bill, and weeded out 800,000 that had entry irregularities. This comes days after he collapsed at a hotel in Nairobi and was placed under intensive care at Nairobi Hospital.